---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy policy, Forward Health"
  description="How Forward Health collects, stores and uses your personal and health information."
>
  <section class="bg-sage-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 py-16 lg:py-20">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-tan-600 mb-4">Privacy policy</p>
      <h1 class="text-charcoal">Your information, looked after.</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-stone leading-relaxed">
        Last updated: May 2026. This page explains how Forward Health Group Pty Ltd ("we", "us")
        handles your personal and health information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 lg:px-8 py-12 lg:py-16 prose-content space-y-10 text-stone leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">What we collect</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">When you book an appointment with us, we collect contact details (name, address, phone, email, date of birth), Medicare and health-fund details where relevant, GP and referrer details, and the clinical information needed to provide your care.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">How we use your information</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">We use your information to provide your treatment, communicate with you about appointments, claim through your health fund (HICAPS, Medicare, DVA, Workcover or NDIS as applicable), and meet our professional and legal obligations. We do not sell your information.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">Where it's stored</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">Your clinical records are stored in Cliniko, our practice management software, which is hosted in Australia. Access is limited to clinicians and reception staff who need it to support your care.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">Sharing your information</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">With your consent, we may share information with your GP, specialist, or other allied health practitioners involved in your care. We do not share your clinical information with anyone else without your written consent, except where we are legally required to do so.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">Accessing or correcting your records</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">You have the right to access your clinical records and request corrections at any time. To do so, contact us by email at <a href="mailto:hello@fwdhealth.com.au" class="text-sage-600 underline">hello@fwdhealth.com.au</a>. We may need to verify your identity before releasing records.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">Concerns or complaints</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">If you have a concern about how we've handled your information, please raise it with us first by emailing the address above. If we can't resolve it together, you may contact the Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC).</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-charcoal text-2xl font-display">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="mt-3">We may update this policy from time to time. The most current version is always published on this page.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
